curam.util.resources

Interface EnvironmentConstants.Trace

  • Enclosing interface:
    EnvironmentConstants

    public static interface EnvironmentConstants.Trace
    These control what diagnostic information (in addition to errors which are always logged) is written to the application server's diagnostics file. Note that you can set the "curam.trace.*" settings independently of the "curam.trace" settings, resulting in the union of these settings.

      • kTraceLevel

        static final java.lang.String kTraceLevel
        Default: trace_off. Tracing is off by default. Turn tracing on by setting the property to trace_on, trace_verbose or trace_ultra_verbose. The value trace_on is equivalent to setting curam.trace.servercalls to true. The value trace_verbose is equivalent to setting curam.trace.servercalls, curam.trace.methods and curam.trace.sql to true, while the highest trace level "trace_ultra_verbose" is equivalent to setting curam.trace.* to true Property name : curam.trace
